president bush on friday awarded the 
presidential citizens medal to ezra taft benson a former 
agriculture adviser to two presidents 
benson a former adviser to presidents franklin d roosevelt and 
dwight eisenhower is one of the most distinguished americans of 
his time the medal citation said 
the utah native was a leader of his church and 60year friend 
of the boy scouts of america the citation said 
benson is president of the mormon church 
the medal is given to people who have performed exemplary deeds 
of service for their country or fellow citizens 
