<TEXT>
a collection of harry s trumans 
personal writings which the former president said could only be 
published after he and his wife had died is set for publication in 
october 
warner books announced the publication date for where the buck 
stops a collection of previously unpublished personal and 
private writings by truman president from 19451953 
in the september issue of writers digest new york literary 
agent scott meredith says he is collaborating with trumans 
daughter margaret truman daniel in editing the writings 
meredith says in his article that the book is blunt and frank 
and honest in typical truman fashion 
chapter titles include why i dont like ike my favorite 
president andrew jackson becoming a world power dropping the 
bomb other chapters treat the american revolution treatment of 
the indians and trumans thoughts on george washington 
</TEXT>
