<TEXT>
hashemi rafsanjani who has become the 
most powerful figure in iran since ayatollah ruhollah khomeini 
died is known to his countrymen as kuseh the shark 
some say it is because of his political ruthlessness cunning 
and business acumen that made him a millionaire all masked behind 
a smile and a sly wit 
others cite a more mundane reason his lack of facial hair 
revealing mongolian ancestry in a nation where beards are a badge 
of revolutionary manhood 
rafsanjanis election to a new more powerful presidency would 
cement the 55yearold clerics hold on power after the death june 
3 of khomeini to whom he was close throughout the decade of 
islamic revolution 
his partnership with incumbent president ayatollah ali khamenei 
the revolutionary patriarchs successor as religious leader is 
considered by many to herald a new era in iranian politics both 
advocate better relations with the west 
constitutional reforms up for approval in the same election 
abolish the office of prime minister and put the president in 
charge of the government answerable only to the parliament 
rafsanjani is a hojatoleslam a cleric of middle rank and has 
been a central figure in khomeinis revolution he was jailed for 
several years under the late shah mohammad reza pahlavi who was 
overthrown in february 1979 
since the revolution rafsanjani is said to have survived 
several assassination attempts and crushed his rivals with brutal 
efficiency 
like many iranian leaders who have seen friends and rivals 
killed in irans deadly political wars rafsanjani travels in an 
armorplated limousine and is surrounded by bodyguards 
he has dominated the parliament as its speaker and built strong 
support in irans critical power centers and among the 
350000member revolutionary guards corps which he briefly 
commanded 
abolhassan banisadr who was irans first president and fled 
when hardliners turned on him in 1981 said before khomeini died 
that rafsanjani ingratiated himself with the patriarch by playing 
the court jester 
hes a man who makes people laugh banisadr said in an 
interview in exile in france its a great art he uses this to 
gain his objectives 
rafsanjani often delivers the sermon a political speech 
more than religious discourse at tehran universitys friday prayer 
sessions 
clutching the barrel of an automatic rifle his white turban 
tilted back on his head he speaks for hours without notes unlike 
other speakers he peppers his sermons with jokes 
banisadr described rafsanjani as a machiavellian figure 
hes a political animal he said hes not brilliant as an 
organizer and he doesnt have too many original ideas but hes a 
manipulator and hes highly intelligent 
during the eightyear war with iraq in which a truce was 
reached last august rafsanjani was khomeinis representative on 
the supreme defense council a nineman board that determined 
military strategy 
he was given control of military affairs in june 1988 charged 
with reversing irans defeats and turning its tired fractious 
forces into an effective fighting machine 
diplomats said rafsanjani had sensed a growing weariness among 
irans 50 million people and believed continuing the war was futile 
amin taheri former editor of the masscirculation tehran daily 
kayhan and now in exile wrote in a recent book rafsanjani a 
conservative in social and economic policy is a radical when it 
comes to the issue of exercising power by revolutionary 
institutions 
taheri described rafsanjani is a master of intrigue and a 
capable tactician 
to many western leaders rafsanjani represents a more acceptable 
face of the islamic revolution because he believes iran needs 
outside help with reconstruction and that most iranians are weary 
of being pariahs 
while rafsanjani appears committed to the fundamentalist 
revolution and its spread his pragmatism some call it 
opportunism sets him apart from most iranian leaders 
he was at the center of the clandestine armsforhostages deal 
with the united states in 198586 and was vulnerable when rivals 
sought to discredit him but with characteristic political agility 
he emerged on top 
rafsanjani was born in behraman a village in rafsanjan province 
on the edge of irans central desert his father was a pistachio 
farmer of moderate means 
khomeini was one of his instructors at the theological seminary 
in the holy city of qom and rafsanjani joined khomeinis 
opposition to the monarchy he helped organize riots in 1963 and 
was instrumental in establishing the network of clerics that became 
khomeinis revolutionary underground 
</TEXT>
