exxons plans in the cleanup of more than 700 miles of 
shoreline damaged by the exxon valdez tanker spill last march 
came under scrutiny this week with the disclosure of an internal 
company memorandum which said no commitment should be made on 
the timing of suspending or resuming cleanup operations 
asked by reporters about the matter at a white house news 
