extensive property does not belong to the people as the opposition 
argued 
the opposition wants a moratorium on sales of party property 
after the communists recently sold some buildings and suggested it 
be divided up so the party enjoy no unfair financial or 
organizational advantages going into the elections 
hungarian opposition activists have complained that in a 
staterun economy it is hard for them to find property and install 
such basic necessities as telephone lines to enable them to compete 
with the communists 
