between 1970 and 1980 the annual rate of population growth in 
rural america was 14 percent compared with 1 percent in urban 
areas 
in the first half of the 1980s rural population grew at an 
annual rate of 07 percent compared with 12 percent in urban 
areas 
during the 70s rural areas experienced a net inmigration of 
about 350000 people each year in contrast there was a net exodus 
of 632000 people in 198586 and 952000 in 198687 
about a third of the 8687 loss was in the 1824 age group 
more than half the adults who left rural areas in that period had 
at least a year of college almost 27 percent had four years 
these figures are from the 1988 rural poverty report by the 
population reference bureau rural refers to nonmetro counties 
those not surrounding large cities about twothirds of the 
nations counties are nonmetro but they have only 23 percent of 
