trust which has had voting control of central newspapers since 
1965 permits the recapitalization as long as it retains at least 
5377 percent voting power 
pulliam quayles grandfather was publisher of the star and 
news he died in 1975 his son eugene s pulliam quayles uncle 
is the current publisher 
under the recapitalization plan the number of shares authorized 
for issuance would be increased from 200000 to 75 million for 
class a stock 20000 to 50 million for class b and 120000 to 25 
million for preferred stock 
