brewer reported an industryleading jump in beer sales that 
contributed to record secondquarter earnings 
the st louisbased company whose brands include budweiser and 
michelob said beer volume has increased 11 million barrels so far 
this year the company sold 214 million barrels of beer during the 
second quarter and 41 million barrels for the first six months 
according to estimates from the beer institute those sales 
accounted for 42 percent of total industry sales for the first six 
months up 14 percent and the largest share gain of any brewer 
our volume growth remains strong and earnings continue to 
benefit from operating efficiencies despite material cost 
increases august a busch iii president and chairman said in a 
statement wednesday 
anheuserbusch reported a 105 percent profit increase for the 
second quarter earnings were 2337 million or 82 cents a share 
up from 2115 million or 72 cents a share the same period last 
year sales increased 68 percent to 248 billion from 232 
billion 
for the year so far the company reported a 101 percent profit 
increase to 4008 million or 140 a share from 3639 million 
or 123 a share sales increased 66 percent to 4685 billion 
from 4396 billion 
our brand families are performing well busch said we are 
particularly pleased with the consumers acceptance of michelob 
dry 
